We are getting low voltages (3.2v) on our Roborio DIO 5v pin when nothing is plugged in. The VRM and Roborio both measure at 12v.

We had working code with not issues and then suddenly the sensors stopped working We are using two different photo sensors, one beam break from Adafruit and one HiLetgo 3pcs E18-D80NK Infrared Photoelectric switch from Amazon. Neither one works with the low voltage but work fine using a backup Roborio.

Any thoughts as to why the low voltage?

First thing to do is check the lightning tab on the driver station and see if it shows any 5v faults. If it does, check for any shorts on the 5v pins on the Rio.

We just had this happen (literally yesterday!) and it did show faults but there was no visible short. We had to swap Rio and will contact NI.

One note though, we saw 0v on the 5v rail but you should always see 3.3 ish between signal and ground. Probably not a wiring issue considering you tried another Rio, but just some food for thought.
